<emphasis id="A6C64659FFF5FFA48778FB49484CFB4B" bold="true" box="[312,377,1158,1184]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Pupa</emphasis>
(based on pharate material). Thorax: cuticle with numerous granules present. Gill (
<figureCitation id="0C8986CEFFF5FFA48708FB604898FB22" box="[328,429,1199,1225]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="27.[264,367,1531,1555]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,326,1507]" captionTargetId="figure-95@27.[264,1323,326,1507]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 10. Pupal gill filaments of Hebridosimulium species (continued). Scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071415" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071415/files/figure.png" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Fig. 10f</figureCitation>
): petioles short and thick; branching pattern (2+2) +2 +2 +2, occasionally (2+2) +2 +2 +1+1; filaments noticeably tapered; maximum length 
<quantity id="534A37AEFFF5FFA48255FB184D93FB1A" box="[1045,1190,1239,1265]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" unit="mm" value="1.6" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.4">1.4–1.8 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="940D9A4BFFF5FFA58778FB3148B1FCFD" blockId="78.[264,1323,1039,1905]" lastBlockId="79.[264,1323,284,790]" lastPageId="79" lastPageNumber="80" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis id="A6C64659FFF5FFA48778FB3148B1FAF3" bold="true" box="[312,388,1278,1304]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Larva</emphasis>
(based on 6 mature last-instar larvae). Body (
<figureCitation id="0C8986CEFFF5FFA485FCFB304D13FAF2" box="[956,1062,1279,1305]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="28.[264,367,1774,1798]" captionTargetBox="[265,1322,406,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-68@28.[265,1322,406,1750]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 11. Left lateral views of Hebridosimulium species larvae. Last-instar larvae, except l &amp; n, which are penultimate. Arrowheads indicate dorsal tubercles. Scale bar = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071417" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071417/files/figure.png" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Fig. 11n</figureCitation>
): total length 
<quantity id="534A37AEFFF5FFA48292FB30480CFAAA" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.7" metricValueMax="6.9" metricValueMin="6.5" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" unit="mm" value="6.7" valueMax="6.9" valueMin="6.5">6.5–6.9 mm</quantity>
; females evenly pale grey dorsally, males pale yellowish-grey with paler intersegmental regions, difference not marked. Head (
<figureCitation id="0C8986CEFFF5FFA485D5FA804ACEFA82" box="[917,1019,1359,1385]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="31.[264,367,1399,1423]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,326,1375]" captionTargetId="figure-179@31.[264,1323,326,1375]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 14. Dorsal views of larval heads of Hebridosimulium species. steatopygium species group. Last instars, except d &amp; f, which are penultimate instars. Scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071423" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071423/files/figure.png" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Fig. 14f</figureCitation>
): both sexes evenly dark brown including labral fan stalks; dorsal head spots negative, but not distinct; sockets of trichoid sensilla pair 5 and 6 markedly pale, darkly aureolate; width 
<quantity id="534A37AEFFF5FFA48268FA504DE0FA52" box="[1064,1237,1439,1465]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.8" metricValueMax="8.2" metricValueMin="7.4" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" unit="mm" value="0.78" valueMax="0.82" valueMin="0.74">0.74–0.82 mm</quantity>
; length 
<quantity id="534A37AEFFF5FFA48748FA08488FFA0A" box="[264,442,1479,1505]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.049999999999999" metricValueMax="8.2" metricValueMin="7.9" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" unit="mm" value="0.8049999999999999" valueMax="0.82" valueMin="0.79">0.79–0.82 mm</quantity>
; distance between antennal bases 
<quantity id="534A37AEFFF5FFA48520FA084D27FA0A" box="[864,1042,1479,1505]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="4.1" metricValueMin="3.9" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" unit="mm" value="0.4" valueMax="0.41" valueMin="0.39">0.39–0.41 mm</quantity>
; ecdysial lines slightly convex, diverged markedly posteriorly, broadly rounded at maximum width; lateral margins of head convex, especially posteriorly; posterior edge of cephalic apotome slightly emarginate; postocciput with fine medial extension. Antenna: total length 
<quantity id="534A37AEFFF5FFA482B7F9F0480CF96A" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5999999999999996" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" unit="mm" value="0.36">0.36 mm</quantity>
; distal article 0.22 times as long as basal articles; markedly shorter than labral fan stalk; distal article dark brown, remainder pale. Labral fan: stalk heavily pigmented anteriorly, anterior palatal bar noticeable, but not markedly protrusive; 39–43 substantial rays, 
<quantity id="534A37AEFFF5FFA48707F910489AF912" box="[327,431,1759,1785]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.4" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" unit="mm" value="0.84">0.84 mm</quantity>
in length, medial rays 
<quantity id="534A37AEFFF5FFA484FBF9104A17F912" box="[699,802,1759,1785]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" unit="mm" value="0.02">0.02 mm</quantity>
in width, 8–10 posterolateral rays finer than others; microtrichia substantial, subequal in length to ray width, pattern distinct, with 4 or 5 shorter microtrichia between those longer. Postgenal cleft (
<figureCitation id="0C8986CEFFF5FFA4826DF8E04DAEF8A2" box="[1069,1179,1839,1865]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="34.[264,367,1395,1419]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,327,1371]" captionTargetId="figure-185@34.[264,1323,326,1371]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 17. Postgenal clefts and hypostoma of larvae of Hebridosimulium species. Last instar except b, d, &amp; f, which are penultimate. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071429" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071429/files/figure.png" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Fig. 17f</figureCitation>
): markedly arrowhead shaped; posterior edges parallel, sharply tapered at mid-length to pointed apex, 1.5 times longer than width; postgenal bridge subequal in length to cleft depth; genae evenly pigmented dark brown, paler around stemmata; ventrolateral elongate muscle spots partially negative. Hypostoma (
<figureCitation id="0C8986CEFFF4FFA584D8FEA34A31FE6D" box="[664,772,364,390]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="36.[264,367,1407,1431]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,326,1379]" captionTargetId="figure-153@36.[264,1323,326,1383]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 19. Hypostomal teeth of larvae of Hebridosimulium species. Last instar, except d &amp; f, which are penultimate. Scale bar = 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071435" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071435/files/figure.png" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Fig. 19f</figureCitation>
): ratio 4.2; median tooth and lateral teeth prominent, latter slightly scalloped medially occasionally directed more laterally, sublateral teeth distinct; paralateral teeth and lateral serrations not obvious; 11–13 substantial hypostomal setae per side. Mandible (
<figureCitation id="0C8986CEFFF4FFA585C9FE2B4AC3FE15" box="[905,1014,484,510]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="43.[264,367,1401,1425]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,327,1377]" captionTargetId="figure-171@43.[264,1323,326,1377]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 21. Mandibular teeth of larvae of Hebridosimulium species, steatopygium species group. Last instar, except d &amp; f, which are penultimate. Scale bar = 0.025 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071439" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071439/files/figure.png" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Fig. 21f</figureCitation>
): apical tooth markedly prominent, preapical and subapical teeth not so; spinous teeth small, gap distinct; serration and sensillum robust and fused basally; blade region smooth and slightly convex. Abdomen: thorax and anterior abdominal segments subequal in width, expanded gradually to maximum width, callipygous posteroventrally; colour pale laterally and ventrally, marked diagonal gray banding laterally on sixth segment; posterodorsal tubercles absent. Posterior circlet: directed ventrally; 170–175 rows of hooks, 29–35 hooks per row (total ca. 5,500).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="940D9A4BFFF4FFA58748FC834B50FC8E" blockId="79.[264,1323,844,950]" box="[264,613,844,869]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">
